<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bark4" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bark,</orth> vb., to cry with the voice of a dog: <bibl n="shak. ven 240" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.383" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 383</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.298" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 298</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.160" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 224</bibl>. Used of a wolf: <bibl n="shak. ven 459" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 459</bibl>; of a fox: <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 55</bibl>. Followed by <cit><quote>at:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 132</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.158" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 158</bibl>. Figuratively: <cit><quote>the envious --ing of your saucy tongue against my lord,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 4, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that thou --est at him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 38</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="78" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>